dbh
------------------------------------------
DBH (acronym for Disk Based Hashtable) is a convenient way to associate
unsigned character keys to data records. Any kind of digital information can
go into the data record, such as text, graphic information, database
structures, you name it. The idea behind using a DBH is build the key index
directly into a multidimensional file format.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.7-1
  cygwin-devel-3.6.7-1
  libdbh-devel-5.0.22-1bl3
  libdbh2-5.0.22-1bl3
  libgdbm6-1.26-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.87.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libgdbm-devel-1.26-1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.87.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://www.gnu.org/software/libdbh/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/dbh/libdbh2-5.0.22.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack dbh-5.0.22-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./dbh-5.0.22-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/dbh-5.0.22-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/dbh-5.0.22-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdbh2-5.0.22-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdbh-devel-5.0.22-X.tar.xz

